To draw a chessboard in LATEX using FEN notation, you can use the 'chessboard4e' package, which provides a comprehensive solution for chessboard graphics. Here's the LATEX code that includes all the required commands and packages:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
\usepackage{chessboard4e}

\begin{document}
\begin{center}
\chessboardsetup{boardfile={empty}, boardsize={8x8}, bordercolor={black}, cellcolor={gray!25,white!75}},
      startpos={fen2position{r1a1/2N3/PPPP1/8/8/PPPP1/RNBQKB1R}},
      orientation={standard}}

\chessboard

\end{center}
\end{document}
```

In this example, we first load the necessary packages:

- `inputenc` for UTF-8 compatibility
- `chessboard4e` for chessboard graphics

We then define a chessboard setup using `chessboardsetup` with the following parameters:

- `boardfile`: set to `empty` because we're providing FEN notation instead of a board file.
